      "note": "**[misc:3]**\n\n~Losing that job resulted be a blessing in disguise~ is not valid because 'resulted' cannot be followed directly by the bare infinitive 'be'. You should use [turned out to be] or [ended up being].\n\n~Losing that job resulted being a blessing in disguise~ is incorrect grammar. The verb 'result' is typically followed by 'in' (e.g., resulted in failure), but to express an outcome, you should use [turned out to be] or [ended up being]."
    },
